yers of American football from California]]\n[[Category:American football quarterbacks]]\n[[Category:Jun\u00edpero Serra High School (San Mateo, California) alumni]]\n[[Category:Michigan Wolverines football players]]\n[[Category:Merrill Lynch people]]\n[[Category:New England Patriots players]]\n[[Category:Tampa Bay Buccaneers players]]\n[[Category:American Conference Pro Bowl players]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl champions]]\n[[Category:Super Bowl MVPs]]\n[[Category:Unconferenced Pro Bowl players]]\n", "name_user": "Historymaj18", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePolitics", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Brady"}
{"title_page": "Isa Briones", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Isa Briones\n| image              = Isa Briones by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            =\n| birth_name         = Isabella Camille Briones\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|1|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[Westminster]], [[London]], England<!-- from her resume; cannot confirm Westminster -->\n| death_date         =\n| death_place        =\n| nationality        = American\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|singer}}\n| years_active       = 2008\u2013present\n| agent              = A3 Artists Agency<!-- see https://resumes.actorsaccess.com/one_page_resume.cfm?custom_link=isa -->\n| credits            = {{plainlist|\n* ''[[Next to Normal]]''\n* ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' (touring production)\n* ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n}}\n| awards             = [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]]\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Jon Jon Briones]]\n*Megan Briones\n}}\n| relatives          = Teo Briones<!-- inclusion notability: https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/teo-briones/credits/304085/ and https://itunes.apple.com/bh/artist/teo-briones/1273413868 et al. -->\n| website            = {{URL|isabriones.com}}\n}}\n'''Isabella Camille Briones'''<ref name=cast>{{cite web|last=Mendoza|first=Ruel J.|url=https://www.pep.ph/news/local/144888/fil-am-actress-isa-briones-joins-cast-of-new-star-trek-spin-off-a748-20190727|title=Fil-Am actress Isa Briones joins cast of new ''Star Trek'' spin-off|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|location=[[Mandaluyong]]|language=English/Tagalog|date=July 27, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> (born January 17, 1999)<ref name=bg>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362057/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> is an English-born American actor and singer. Briones began her career as a model in New York City at age three; she began acting in feature films and stage productions in 2008, after her family moved to Los Angeles.\n\nBriones won an [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] for her stage performance in ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in 2018. The same year, she auditioned for and won a spot in the cast of the touring production of ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'', playing multiple roles. In 2019, she was cast in multiple roles in the television series ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'', for which she also sang an updated version of an [[Irving Berlin]] song.\n\n== Early life ==\nBriones was born in London to [[Jon Jon Briones|Jon Jon]] and Megan Briones ({{nee}} Johnson), and she has a younger brother, Teo.<ref name=bww>{{cite web|last1=Grigware|first1=Don|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones Opens Up About ''Next to Normal''|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/los-angeles/article/BWW-Interview-ISA-BRIONES-Opens-Up-About-NEXT-TO-NORMAL-20160819|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020|language=en|date=August 19, 2016}}</ref> Her family are all musical theatre actors;<ref name=blueskies/> her father was closing the original [[West End theatre]] production of ''[[Miss Saigon]]'' when Briones was born.<ref name=bww/> Briones's father is [[Filipinos|Filipino]]; her mother, [[Irish people|Irish]] and [[Swedes|Swedish]].<ref name=bg/><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Weinberg|first=Lindsay|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/isa-briones-star-trek-picards-progressive-asian-american-representation-1272115|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Actress on Show's 'Progressive' Asian-American Representation|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 22, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones was ten months old when her family moved from London to New York City, where she began work as a model at age three. In 2006, when Briones was seven, her family moved to Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/><!-- cites previous 2 sentences --> Briones learned acting and singing at home from her parents; she also attended the [[Los Angeles County High School for the Arts]], majoring in both theatre and musical theatre.<ref name=bg2/>\n\n== Career ==\n===Film and television===\nBriones began her acting career as a child in 2008, appearing in television commercials and playing supporting roles in feature films including ''Brown Soup Thing'' and ''[[Takers]]''.<ref name=cast/><!-- cites films --><ref name=ovation/><!-- Ginell cites commercials -->\n{{listen\n| filename    = Briones Isa \u2013 Blue Skies 33s.ogg\n| title       = \"Blue Skies\"\n| description = Isa Briones was asked by ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] and composer [[Jeff Russo]] to sing \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" for the season one finale.\n| pos         = right\n}}\nIn 2019,<ref>{{cite news|last=Petski|first=Denise|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/star-trek-jean-luc-picard-alison-pill-harry-treadaway-isa-briones-cast-1202597412/|title=''Star Trek'' Jean-Luc Picard Series Adds Alison Pill, Harry Treadaway & Isa Briones To Cast|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Briones was cast in ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' in multiple roles, playing two sets of [[synthetic biology#synthetic life|synthetic]] twins: Dahj and Soji, and Jana and Sutra.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Pirrello|first=Phil|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/11-star-trek-picard-easter-eggs-penultimate-episode-1285313|title=11 'Star Trek: Picard' Easter Eggs as Season 1 Nears the End|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref> Briones sent tapes of herself to audition for ''Picard'' while she was playing multiple roles in a stage production,<ref name=paste/> and called upon that experience in portraying her characters. She most closely identified with Soji: \"Being a mixed person you go through life with this constant inner struggle ... of coming to terms with who you are, not according to what other people tell you\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Hegedus|first=Eric|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/26/star-trek-picard-season-1-finale-gives-jean-luc-a-shocking-new-reality/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Season 1 finale gives Jean-Luc a shocking new reality|newspaper=[[New York Post]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><!-- cites previous 2 sentences -->\n\nFor the season one finale, \"[[Star_Trek:_Picard#Episodes|Et In Arcadia Ego, Part 2]]\", [[Irving Berlin]]'s \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was set to play during [[Data (Star Trek)|Data]]'s final scene as a bookend to him performing the song in ''[[Star Trek: Nemesis]]''. [[Jeff Russo]] composed a new arrangement and planned to find a vocalist, until series co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] mentioned that \"Isa is a singer.\"<ref name=blueskies>{{cite AV media|url=https://intl.startrek.com/videos/star-trek-picard-and-the-return-of-blue-skies|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' and The Return of \"Blue Skies\"|type=Television production|publisher=startrek.com|accessdate=April 3, 2020|quote=[Briones:] This is obviously a bit of a throwback to ... when Data sang 'Blue Skies', so it's really cool that Data's 'daughter' kind of gets to sing it as well (Briones' characters are synthetic beings created from a neuron saved after Data's death).}}</ref><!-- cites previous 2 sentences --><!-- see https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2020/01/28/star-trek-picard-is-everything-i-didnt-know-i-wanted-it-to-be/ -->{{efn|She was able to watch a rough cut of the scene while recording the song, \"bringing me to tears.\"<ref name=paste>{{cite magazine|last=Miller|first=Liz Shannon|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/tv/star-trek-picard/ending-explained-isa-briones/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Star Isa Briones on the Finale, Confirms Patrick Stewart Is 'Just the Coolest Dude'|magazine=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>}}\n\n===Theatre===\nBriones has performed in numerous stage musicals. She earned three separate [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] nominations for Featured Actress In a Musical from the LA STAGE Alliance in 2018; she won for her work as Natalie in the [[East West Players]] production of ''[[Next to Normal]]'', topping her own performance as \"[[Juan Per\u00f3n|Per\u00f3n]]'s mistress\" in ''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''.<ref name=ovation>{{cite news|last=Gelt|first=Jessica|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-sm-ovation-awards-2018-story.html|title=Ovation Awards 2018: Wins for Actors Co-op's ''33 Variations'', East West Players' ''Next to Normal''|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 30, 2018|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites award/nominations.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|last=Ginell|first=Cary|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/thousand-oaks/article/BWW-Interview-Isa-Briones-of-EVITA-at-Cabrillo-Music-Theatre-20161020|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones of ''Evita'' at Cabrillo Music Theatre|publisher=[[BroadwayWorld]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites role in ''Evita''.}}</ref><!-- combines to cite graf -->\n\nBriones joined her father when he moved back to New York in January 2018.<ref name=ovation/><!-- see Ginell --> At age 19, she was cast in the musical ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' following a seven-month audition process, becoming the youngest person to join the national touring production, in which she played both Peggy Schuyler and Maria Reynolds.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://usa.inquirer.net/11701/fil-isa-briones-youngest-actor-hamilton-natl-tour |title=Fil-Am Isa Briones is youngest actor in ''Hamilton'' nat\u2019l tour |last=Ang |first=Walter |date=April 19, 2018 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|access-date=February 9, 2020 }}</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences -->\n\n===Music===\nBeginning in 2018, fellow Filipino-American performer AJ Rafael released several video duets with Briones.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Briong|first=Ian|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362306/youtube-star-aj-rafael-thanks-fans-since-middle-school-in-open-letter-releases-new-song-and-music-video|title=YouTube star AJ Rafael thanks 'fans since middle school' in open letter ...|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=February 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites Filipino-American.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/ilajil/search?query=isa+briones|title=AJ Rafael (official channel)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites videos.}}</ref> Their version of \"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\" from ''[[The Greatest Showman]]'' was released as a single.<ref name=RtS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/rewrite-the-stars-feat-isa-briones-single/1362917450|title=AJ Rafael: Rewrite the Stars (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 23, 2018|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nHer rendition of \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was released as a single in 2020.<ref name=BS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/blue-skies-feat-isa-briones-single/1504773372|title=Blue Skies (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' called Briones the \"breakout star\" of ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in May 2017, noting that she was familiar with the role of Natalie and \"has a lock on it.\"<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Gray|first=Margaret|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-next-to-normal-review-20170526-story.html|title=Review: At East West Players, the gut-wrenching emotion of ''Next to Normal'' transcends race|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|url-access=subscription|date=May 25, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020|postscript=. Gray called Briones \"the lovely, impressive newcomer\" in her review the year before.}}</ref>\n\nHer dual performances in ''Hamilton'' brought praise from the ''[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]'': she \"effectively plays Peggy Schuyler as a cupcake and Maria Reynolds as a flamb\u00e9.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Newmark|first=Judith|url=https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/arts-and-theatre/reviews/hamilton-rises-up-to-the-highest-reaches-at-the-fox/article_e54a88c3-01ba-5efa-9b52-12fa7e6e55a6.html|title=''Hamilton'' rises up to the highest reaches at the Fox Theatre|newspaper=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]|date=April 5, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]'' wrote, \"Briones brings a sultry alto to her second role as Maria Reynolds,\" Hamilton's mistress.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Pender|first=Rick|url=https://www.citybeat.com/arts-culture/theater/article/21048364/the-hamilton-cincinnati-staging-is-on-par-with-broadways-original|title=The ''Hamilton'' Cincinnati Staging is on Par with Broadway's Original|newspaper=[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]|date=February 22, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> She played Reynolds \"convincingly as a depressive, allergic to truth-telling\", wrote DC Theatre Scene.<ref>{{cite web|last=Treanor|first=Tim|url=https://dctheatrescene.com/2018/06/15/review-why-hamilton-is-the-greatest-musical-yet-written/|title=Review: Why ''Hamilton'' is the greatest musical yet written|publisher=DC Theatre Scene|date=June 15, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOf her work in ''Star Trek: Picard'', ''[[IGN]]'' wrote that Soji is effectively a plot device, but Briones \"gives it her all week after week, reacting best she can to Soji\u2019s changing status quo\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Collura|first=Scott|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/star-trek-picard-episode-9-recap-review-et-in-arcadia-ego-part-1|title=Star Trek: Picard Episode 9 Recap / Review \u2013 \"Et in Arcadia Ego, Part 1\"|website=[[IGN]]|location=[[San Francisco]]|date=March 28, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called the plot developments \"shock tactics, stranding newcomer Briones in [a] vacant role\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Franich|first=Darren|url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2020/01/23/star-trek-picard-review/|title=Can ''Star Trek: Picard'' recover from its bafflingly bad premiere?|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> Soji is \"underwritten ... but [Briones] acquits herself well\", wrote [[/Film]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Todd|first=Andrew|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/picard-season-1-spoiler-review/|title=5 Things We Loved About \u2018Star Trek: Picard\u2019 Season 1 (And 3 Things We Hated)|publisher=[[/Film]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Tor.com]]'' said her performance improved with each episode; \"her confused post-activation Soji is her best work\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=DeCandido|first=Keith R. A.|url=https://www.tor.com/2020/04/03/regrets-ive-had-a-few-star-trek-picard-first-season-overview/|title=Regrets, I've Had a Few \u2014 ''Star Trek: Picard'' First Season Overview|magazine=[[Tor.com]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAs of 2020, Briones lives in Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/> She has begun making music with her brother Teo.<ref name=bg2>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362175/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21-conclusion|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21 (conclusion)|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones joined her ''Picard'' castmates including [[Jonathan Frakes]], [[Jeri Ryan]] and [[Brent Spiner]] in a video message of hope to viewers affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] in April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Zinski|first=Dan|url=https://screenrant.com/star-trek-picard-discovery-cast-video-coronavirus/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' & ''Discovery'' Casts Unite For Hopeful Message|website=[[Screen Rant]]|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==<!-- see ref cast -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|''Brown Soup Thing''\n|Cousin Isa\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Takers]]''\n|Sunday\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2013\n|''Lonely Boy''\n|Mia\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Assassination of Gianni Versace: American Crime Story]]''\n|Elena Cunanan\n|Television series; also starring [[Jon Jon Briones]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n| Dahj Asha / Soji Asha / Sutra\n|Television series\n|-\n| ''[[The Ready Room]]''\n| Herself\n| Television aftershow: \"Episode 22\"\n|}\n\n==Discography==<!-- see refs RtS and BS -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Singles\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Label\n|-\n|2018\n|\"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\"\n|AJ Rafael ft. Isa Briones\n|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n|-\n|2020\n|\"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\"\n|Isa Briones\n|[[Lakeshore Entertainment|Lakeshore]]\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Ovation Awards===<!-- see ref ovation -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Nominated Work\n!Role\n!Category\n!Result\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''\n|\"Per\u00f3n's Mistress\"\n|Featured Actress In a Musical\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Next to Normal]]'' (East West Players)\n|Natalie\n|Featured Actress In a Musical\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Next to Normal]]'' (Triage and Standing Room Only Prods.)\n|Natalie\n|Featured Actress In a Musical\n|{{nom}}\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|2976800|Isa Briones}}\n* [https://www.isabriones.com/ Official website]\n\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:Actresses from California]]\n[[Category:American actresses of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:American musical theatre actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Filipino descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Swedish descent]]\n[[Category:American singers of Asian descent]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles County High School for the Arts alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Isa Briones\n| image              = Isa Briones by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            =\n| birth_name         = Isabella Camille Briones\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1999|1|17}}\n| birth_place        = [[Westminster]], [[London]], England<!-- from her resume; cannot confirm Westminster -->\n| death_date         =\n| death_place        =\n| nationality        = American\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|singer}}\n| years_active       = 2008\u2013present\n| agent              = A3 Artists Agency<!-- see https://resumes.actorsaccess.com/one_page_resume.cfm?custom_link=isa -->\n| credits            = {{plainlist|\n* ''[[Next to Normal]]''\n* ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' (touring production)\n* ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n}}\n| awards             = [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]]\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n*[[Jon Jon Briones]]\n*Megan Briones\n}}\n| relatives          = Teo Briones<!-- inclusion notability: https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/teo-briones/credits/304085/ and https://itunes.apple.com/bh/artist/teo-briones/1273413868 et al. -->\n| website            = {{URL|isabriones.com}}\n}}\n'''Isabella Camille Briones'''<ref name=cast>{{cite web|last=Mendoza|first=Ruel J.|url=https://www.pep.ph/news/local/144888/fil-am-actress-isa-briones-joins-cast-of-new-star-trek-spin-off-a748-20190727|title=Fil-Am actress Isa Briones joins cast of new ''Star Trek'' spin-off|publisher=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|location=[[Mandaluyong]]|language=English/Tagalog|date=July 27, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> (born January 17, 1999)<ref name=bg>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362057/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 30, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> is an English-born American actor and singer. Briones began her career as a model in New York City at age three; she began acting in feature films and stage productions in 2008, after her family moved to Los Angeles.\n\nBriones won an [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] for her stage performance in ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in 2018. The same year, she auditioned for and won a spot in the cast of the touring production of ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'', playing multiple roles. In 2019, she was cast in multiple roles in the television series ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'', for which she also sang an updated version of an [[Irving Berlin]] song.\n\n== Early life ==\nBriones was born in London to [[Jon Jon Briones|Jon Jon]] and Megan Briones ({{nee}} Johnson), and she has a younger brother, Teo.<ref name=bww>{{cite web|last1=Grigware|first1=Don|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones Opens Up About ''Next to Normal''|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/los-angeles/article/BWW-Interview-ISA-BRIONES-Opens-Up-About-NEXT-TO-NORMAL-20160819|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|accessdate=April 9, 2020|language=en|date=August 19, 2016}}</ref> Her family are all musical theatre actors;<ref name=blueskies/> her father was closing the original [[West End theatre]] production of ''[[Miss Saigon]]'' when Briones was born.<ref name=bww/> Briones's father is [[Filipinos|Filipino]]; her mother, [[Irish people|Irish]] and [[Swedes|Swedish]].<ref name=bg/><ref>{{Cite magazine|last=Weinberg|first=Lindsay|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/rambling-reporter/isa-briones-star-trek-picards-progressive-asian-american-representation-1272115|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Actress on Show's 'Progressive' Asian-American Representation|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=January 22, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones was ten months old when her family moved from London to New York City, where she began work as a model at age three. In 2006, when Briones was seven, her family moved to Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/><!-- cites previous 2 sentences --> Briones learned acting and singing at home from her parents; she also attended the [[Los Angeles County High School for the Arts]], majoring in both theatre and musical theatre.<ref name=bg2/>\n\n== Career ==\n===Film and television===\nBriones began her acting career as a child in 2008, appearing in television commercials and playing supporting roles in feature films including ''Brown Soup Thing'' and ''[[Takers]]''.<ref name=cast/><!-- cites films --><ref name=ovation/><!-- Ginell cites commercials -->\n{{listen\n| filename    = Briones Isa \u2013 Blue Skies 33s.ogg\n| title       = \"Blue Skies\"\n| description = Isa Briones was asked by ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] and composer [[Jeff Russo]] to sing \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" for the season one finale.\n| pos         = right\n}}\nIn 2019,<ref>{{cite news|last=Petski|first=Denise|url=https://deadline.com/2019/04/star-trek-jean-luc-picard-alison-pill-harry-treadaway-isa-briones-cast-1202597412/|title=''Star Trek'' Jean-Luc Picard Series Adds Alison Pill, Harry Treadaway & Isa Briones To Cast|publisher=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=April 17, 2019|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref> Briones was cast in ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]'' in multiple roles, playing two sets of [[synthetic biology#synthetic life|synthetic]] twins: Dahj and Soji, and Jana and Sutra.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Pirrello|first=Phil|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/11-star-trek-picard-easter-eggs-penultimate-episode-1285313|title=11 'Star Trek: Picard' Easter Eggs as Season 1 Nears the End|magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 19, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref> Briones sent tapes of herself to audition for ''Picard'' while she was playing multiple roles in a stage production,<ref name=paste/> and called upon that experience in portraying her characters. She most closely identified with Soji: \"Being a mixed person you go through life with this constant inner struggle ... of coming to terms with who you are, not according to what other people tell you\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Hegedus|first=Eric|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/26/star-trek-picard-season-1-finale-gives-jean-luc-a-shocking-new-reality/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Season 1 finale gives Jean-Luc a shocking new reality|newspaper=[[New York Post]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref><!-- cites previous 2 sentences -->\n\nFor the season one finale, \"[[Star_Trek:_Picard#Episodes|Et In Arcadia Ego, Part 2]]\", [[Irving Berlin]]'s \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was set to play during [[Data (Star Trek)|Data]]'s final scene as a bookend to him performing the song in ''[[Star Trek: Nemesis]]''; [[Jeff Russo]] composed a new arrangement and planned to find a vocalist, until series co-creator [[Alex Kurtzman]] mentioned that \"Isa is a singer.\"<ref name=blueskies>{{cite AV media|url=https://intl.startrek.com/videos/star-trek-picard-and-the-return-of-blue-skies|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' and The Return of \"Blue Skies\"|type=Television production|publisher=startrek.com|accessdate=April 3, 2020|quote=[Briones:] This is obviously a bit of a throwback to ... when Data sang 'Blue Skies', so it's really cool that Data's 'daughter' kind of gets to sing it as well (Briones' characters are synthetic beings created from a neuron saved after Data's death).}}</ref><!-- cites previous 2 sentences --><!-- see https://www.forbes.com/sites/erikkain/2020/01/28/star-trek-picard-is-everything-i-didnt-know-i-wanted-it-to-be/ -->{{efn|She was able to watch a rough cut of the scene while recording the song, \"bringing me to tears.\"<ref name=paste>{{cite magazine|last=Miller|first=Liz Shannon|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/tv/star-trek-picard/ending-explained-isa-briones/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' Star Isa Briones on the Finale, Confirms Patrick Stewart Is 'Just the Coolest Dude'|magazine=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>}}\n\n===Theatre===\nBriones has performed in numerous stage musicals. She earned three separate [[Ovation Awards|Ovation Award]] nominations for Featured Actress In a Musical from the LA STAGE Alliance in 2018; she won for her work as Natalie in the [[East West Players]] production of ''[[Next to Normal]]'', topping her own performance as \"[[Juan Per\u00f3n|Per\u00f3n]]'s mistress\" in ''[[Evita (musical)|Evita]]''.<ref name=ovation>{{cite news|last=Gelt|first=Jessica|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-sm-ovation-awards-2018-story.html|title=Ovation Awards 2018: Wins for Actors Co-op's ''33 Variations'', East West Players' ''Next to Normal''|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=January 30, 2018|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites award/nominations.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|last=Ginell|first=Cary|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/thousand-oaks/article/BWW-Interview-Isa-Briones-of-EVITA-at-Cabrillo-Music-Theatre-20161020|title=BWW Interview: Isa Briones of ''Evita'' at Cabrillo Music Theatre|publisher=[[BroadwayWorld]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=April 10, 2020|postscript=. Cites role in ''Evita''.}}</ref><!-- combines to cite graf -->\n\nBriones joined her father when he moved back to New York in January 2018.<ref name=ovation/><!-- see Ginell --> At age 19, she was cast in the musical ''[[Hamilton (musical)|Hamilton]]'' following a seven-month audition process, becoming the youngest person to join the national touring production, in which she played both Peggy Schuyler and Maria Reynolds.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://usa.inquirer.net/11701/fil-isa-briones-youngest-actor-hamilton-natl-tour |title=Fil-Am Isa Briones is youngest actor in ''Hamilton'' nat\u2019l tour |last=Ang |first=Walter |date=April 19, 2018 |work=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|access-date=February 9, 2020 }}</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences -->\n\n===Music===\nBeginning in 2018, fellow Filipino-American performer AJ Rafael released several video duets with Briones.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Briong|first=Ian|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362306/youtube-star-aj-rafael-thanks-fans-since-middle-school-in-open-letter-releases-new-song-and-music-video|title=YouTube star AJ Rafael thanks 'fans since middle school' in open letter ...|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=February 1, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites Filipino-American.}}{{indent|2}}{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/user/ilajil/search?query=isa+briones|title=AJ Rafael (official channel)|publisher=[[YouTube]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|postscript=. Cites videos.}}</ref> Their version of \"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\" from ''[[The Greatest Showman]]'' was released as a single.<ref name=RtS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/rewrite-the-stars-feat-isa-briones-single/1362917450|title=AJ Rafael: Rewrite the Stars (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 23, 2018|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nHer rendition of \"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\" was released as a single in 2020.<ref name=BS>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/blue-skies-feat-isa-briones-single/1504773372|title=Blue Skies (feat. Isa Briones) \u2013 Single|publisher=[[Apple Music]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' called Briones the \"breakout star\" of ''[[Next to Normal]]'' in May 2017, noting that she was familiar with the role of Natalie and \"has a lock on it.\"<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Gray|first=Margaret|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/la-et-cm-next-to-normal-review-20170526-story.html|title=Review: At East West Players, the gut-wrenching emotion of ''Next to Normal'' transcends race|newspaper=[[Los Angeles Times]]|url-access=subscription|date=May 25, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020|postscript=. Gray called Briones \"the lovely, impressive newcomer\" in her review the year before.}}</ref>\n\nHer dual performances in ''Hamilton'' brought praise from the ''[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]'': she \"effectively plays Peggy Schuyler as a cupcake and Maria Reynolds as a flamb\u00e9.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Newmark|first=Judith|url=https://www.stltoday.com/entertainment/arts-and-theatre/reviews/hamilton-rises-up-to-the-highest-reaches-at-the-fox/article_e54a88c3-01ba-5efa-9b52-12fa7e6e55a6.html|title=''Hamilton'' rises up to the highest reaches at the Fox Theatre|newspaper=[[St. Louis Post-Dispatch]]|date=April 5, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]'' wrote, \"Briones brings a sultry alto to her second role as Maria Reynolds,\" Hamilton's mistress.<ref>{{cite newspaper|last=Pender|first=Rick|url=https://www.citybeat.com/arts-culture/theater/article/21048364/the-hamilton-cincinnati-staging-is-on-par-with-broadways-original|title=The ''Hamilton'' Cincinnati Staging is on Par with Broadway's Original|newspaper=[[Cincinnati CityBeat]]|date=February 22, 2019|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> She played Reynolds \"convincingly as a depressive, allergic to truth-telling\", wrote DC Theatre Scene.<ref>{{cite web|last=Treanor|first=Tim|url=https://dctheatrescene.com/2018/06/15/review-why-hamilton-is-the-greatest-musical-yet-written/|title=Review: Why ''Hamilton'' is the greatest musical yet written|publisher=DC Theatre Scene|date=June 15, 2018|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOf her work in ''Star Trek: Picard'', ''[[IGN]]'' wrote that Soji is effectively a plot device, but Briones \"gives it her all week after week, reacting best she can to Soji\u2019s changing status quo\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Collura|first=Scott|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/star-trek-picard-episode-9-recap-review-et-in-arcadia-ego-part-1|title=Star Trek: Picard Episode 9 Recap / Review \u2013 \"Et in Arcadia Ego, Part 1\"|website=[[IGN]]|location=[[San Francisco]]|date=March 28, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' called the plot developments \"shock tactics, stranding newcomer Briones in [a] vacant role\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Franich|first=Darren|url=https://ew.com/tv-reviews/2020/01/23/star-trek-picard-review/|title=Can ''Star Trek: Picard'' recover from its bafflingly bad premiere?|magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=January 23, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> Soji is \"underwritten ... but [Briones] acquits herself well\", wrote [[/Film]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Todd|first=Andrew|url=https://www.slashfilm.com/picard-season-1-spoiler-review/|title=5 Things We Loved About \u2018Star Trek: Picard\u2019 Season 1 (And 3 Things We Hated)|publisher=[[/Film]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Tor.com]]'' said her performance improved with each episode; \"her confused post-activation Soji is her best work\".<ref>{{cite magazine|last=DeCandido|first=Keith R. A.|url=https://www.tor.com/2020/04/03/regrets-ive-had-a-few-star-trek-picard-first-season-overview/|title=Regrets, I've Had a Few \u2014 ''Star Trek: Picard'' First Season Overview|magazine=[[Tor.com]]|date=April 3, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAs of 2020, Briones lives in Los Angeles.<ref name=bg/> She has begun making music with her brother Teo.<ref name=bg2>{{cite newspaper|last=Nepales|first=Ruben V.|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/362175/fil-am-isa-briones-went-from-hamilton-to-a-female-lead-role-in-picard-and-shes-just-21-conclusion|title=Fil-Am Isa Briones went from ''Hamilton'' to a female lead role in ''Picard''\u2014and she\u2019s just 21 (conclusion)|newspaper=[[Philippine Daily Inquirer]]|location=[[Makati]]|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBriones joined her ''Picard'' castmates including [[Jonathan Frakes]], [[Jeri Ryan]] and [[Brent Spiner]] in a video message of hope to viewers affected by the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] in April 2020.<ref>{{cite web|last=Zinski|first=Dan|url=https://screenrant.com/star-trek-picard-discovery-cast-video-coronavirus/|title=''Star Trek: Picard'' & ''Discovery'' Casts Unite For Hopeful Message|website=[[Screen Rant]]|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==<!-- see ref cast -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|''Brown Soup Thing''\n|Cousin Isa\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2010\n|''[[Takers]]''\n|Sunday\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2013\n|''Lonely Boy''\n|Mia\n|Feature film\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[The Assassination of Gianni Versace: American Crime Story]]''\n|Elena Cunanan\n|Television series; also starring [[Jon Jon Briones]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2020\n| ''[[Star Trek: Picard]]''\n| Dahj Asha / Soji Asha / Sutra\n|Television series\n|-\n| ''[[The Ready Room]]''\n| Herself\n| Television aftershow: \"Episode 22\"\n|}\n\n==Discography==<!-- see refs RtS and BS -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Singles\n|-\n!Year\n!Title\n!Artist\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Label\n|-\n|2018\n|\"[[Rewrite the Stars]]\"\n|AJ Rafael ft. Isa Briones\n|[[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]\n|-\n|2020\n|\"[[Blue Skies (Irving Berlin song)|Blue Skies]]\"\n|Isa Briones\n|[[Lakeshore Entertainment|Lakeshore]]\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Ovation Awards===<!-- see ref ovation -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Nomi