62|attempted military coup (1962)]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"Coup\"/><ref name=\"royalthomian\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Rex|De Costa}}\n| [[Lieutenant Colonel]], Commanding officer, [[Ruhunu Regiment]], Vice President, [[World Veterans Federation]] (1961&ndash;1963)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|}\n\n===Navy===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:*;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:65%;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notability\n! style=\"width:*;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Reference(s)\n|-\n| {{sortname|Basil|Gunasekara}}\n| [[Admiral]], [[Commander of the Navy (Sri Lanka)|Commander of Navy]] (1973&ndash;1979)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"commanders\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Thisara|Samarasinghe}}\n| [[Admiral]], [[Commander of the Navy (Sri Lanka)|Commander of Navy]] (2009\u20132011)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"RCcom\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.island.lk/2009/07/13/news20.html |title=Army, Navy get new commanders |publisher=Island.lk |date= |accessdate=10 September 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ravindra|Wijegunaratne}}\n| [[Admiral]], [[Chief of the Defence Staff (Sri Lanka)|Chief of the Defence Staff]] (2017&ndash;present), [[Commander of the Navy (Sri Lanka)|Commander of Navy]] (2015&ndash;2017), Director General of the [[Sri Lanka Coast Guard]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.navy.lk/index.php?id=949 |title=Two Intakes of Sailors pass out at SLNS Nipuna |publisher=Navy.lk |date=15 August 2008 |accessdate=10 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111103005252/http://www.navy.lk/index.php?id=949 |archivedate=3 November 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Asoka|de Silva (admiral)}}\n| [[Vice Admiral]], [[Commander of the Navy (Sri Lanka)|Commander of Navy]] (1983&ndash;1986)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref name=\"commanders\"/>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Rajan|Kadiragamar}}\n| [[Rear Admiral]], [[Commander of the Navy (Sri 