ent Member of Parliament\n\n====Former====\n;Post-Independence\n* [[Sir]] [[Frank Gunasekera]] \u2013 Deputy President of the [[Senate of Ceylon]]\n* [[E.W.Perera]] \u2013 [[Senate of Ceylon|Senator]], member of the State Council and the Legislative Council (note: also listed in Prominent figures in the Independence Movement)\n* [[E. B. Wikramanayake]] {{post-nominals|QC}} \u2013 former Senator and Cabinet Minister of Justice\n* [[A. P. Jayasuriya]] \u2013 former Senator, Cabinet Minister of Health and Member of Parliament\n* [[Sarath Wijesinghe]] \u2013 former Senator, Cabinet Minister of Nationalised Services and Senator\n* [[Justin Kotalawela]] \u2013 former Senator and Member of the State Council\n* [[Somasundaram Nadesan]] {{post-nominals|QC}} \u2013 former Senator<ref>[http://www.tamilnation.org/nadesan/moldrich.htm This Man Nadesan: a Biographical Sketch]{{dead link|date=September 2011}}</ref> (note: also listed in Lawyers)\n* [[V.R. Schockman]] \u2013 former Senator (note: also listed in Mayors, Sportsmen and sports administrators)\n* [[R.S.V. Poulier]] {{post-nominals|CBE}} <small>[[Ceylon Civil Service|CCS]]</small> \u2013 former Senator and Member of Parliament\n* [[L. L. Hunter]] {{post-nominals|post-noms=[[Companion of the Order of St Michael and St George|CMG]]|[[Ceylon Civil Service|CCS]]}} - former Parliamentary Secretary, Senator and Member of Parliament\n* [[C. Coomaraswamy]] <small>[[Ceylon Civil Service|CCS]]</small> \u2013 former Senator (note: also listed in Civil servants, Diplomats)\n* [[Lalith Athulathmudali]] <small>[[President's Counsel (Sri Lanka)|PC]]</small> \u2013 former Cabinet Minister of National Security & Defence, Minister of Agriculture, Minister of Education, Member of Parliament\n* [[Anura Bandaranaike]] \u2013 former Cabinet [[Minister of Foreign Affairs of Sri Lanka|Minister of Foreign Affairs]], Tourism, Industry, Investment & National Heritage, [[Leader of the Opposition (Sri Lanka)|Leader of the Opposition]], Member of Par