hchi |publisher=Dailynews.lk |date=1 June 2009 |accessdate=10 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110916065912/http://www.dailynews.lk/2009/06/01/sec02.asp |archivedate=16 September 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Parakrama|Pannipitiya}}\n| [[Major General]] [[Security Forces Headquarters - East|Commander Security Forces Headquarters \u2013 East]] (2007&ndash;2008)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Athula|Jayawardane}}\n| [[Major General]], [[Security Forces Headquarters \u2013 Mullaitivu|Commander Security Forces Headquarters \u2013 Mullaitivu]], [[Master-General of the Ordnance (Sri Lanka)|Master-General of the Ordnance]], Director Operations, [[General Staff]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sundaytimes.lk/100131/News/nws_02.html |title=Major shuffle in the Army after poll victory |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date= |accessdate=23 February 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Devinda|Kalupahana}}\n| [[Major General]], Director Operations [[General Staff]], Commandant [[Sri Lanka Military Academy]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armouredcorps.lk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=67:major-general-d-kalupahana-rsp-usp-psc&catid=7:retaired-senior-officers&Itemid=4 |title=Major General D Kalupahana RSP USP psc |publisher=Armouredcorps.lk |accessdate=10 September 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110904092011/http://www.armouredcorps.lk/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=67%3Amajor-general-d-kalupahana-rsp-usp-psc&catid=7%3Aretaired-senior-officers&Itemid=4 |archivedate=4 September 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|C. H.|Fernando}}\n| [[Major General]], Director Operations [[General Staff]], Commandant [[Sri Lanka Military Academy|Army Training Centre]], Commander [[Security Forces Headquarters \u2013 Jaffna|Northern Command]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.armouredcorps.lk/index.ph