erawarana}}\n| Founder/chairman/CEO [[WSO2]] Inc., founding member [[Lanka Software Foundation]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Arjuna|Sittampalam}}\n| Author, [[Investment Banker]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ranji|Salgado}}\n| Economist, senior [[International Monetary Fund]] official\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/090920/Plus/plus_07.html |title=A leading light in the field of economics |publisher=Sundaytimes.lk |date= |accessdate=10 September 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sortname|Dulith|Herath}}\n| Entrepreneur, founder and chairman of e-commerce organization, kapruka.com\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|}\n\n==Sports==\n\n===Sports administrators===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:*;\" | Name\n! style=\"width:65%;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notability\n! style=\"width:*;\" class=\"unsortable\" | Reference(s)\n|-\n| {{sortname|V. R.|Schockman}}\n| First President of the [[National Olympic Committee of Sri Lanka|Ceylon Olympic and Empire Games Association]] (current National Olympic Committee of Sri Lanka) (note: also listed in Legislators)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|Donald|Obeyesekere}}\n| Former President of the [[National Olympic Committee of Sri Lanka|National Olympic Committee of Ceylon]] (note: also listed in Legislators)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n|{{sortname|Edward|Grey (policemen)}}\n| Former Secretary of the [[National Olympic Committee of Sri Lanka|National Olympic Committee of Ceylon]] (note: also listed in Police)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|A. E.|Christoffelsz}}\n| Former President of the [[Sri Lanka Cricket|Board of Control for Cricket]] (1950\u20131952)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n|-\n| {{sortname|B. R.|Heyn}}\n| Former President of the [[Sri Lanka Cricket|Board of Control for Cricket]] (1976\u20131978), Ceylon cricketer (note: also listed in Military)\